The paper deals with the problem of leader election in distributed computing, which is a fundamental problem in the field of Distributed Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the concept of anonymous networks, which falls under the category of Distributed Systems (cs.DS). The paper uses information theory to establish tradeoffs between the allocated time and the amount of information that has to be given a priori to the nodes, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the concept of oracles, which is a common topic in Network Information Theory (cs.NI). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of time complexity, which falls under the category of Computational Complexity (cs.SI).
